## 4. Content Creation (COPY-PASTE READY, Deep)

All content MUST be ready to paste. User does NOT edit.

### Content per Goal

#### 💰 Revenue Content Formula
```
AIDA Framework:
A - Attention: Hook with pain point stat
I - Interest: "Imagine if..." scenario
D - Desire: Show benefits + social proof
A - Action: Clear CTA with urgency

Example:
"🔥 [Stat about problem]
Imagine if [benefit scenario].
[Product] helps you [specific outcome].
[Social proof: "500+ users in first week"]
👉 [CTA with urgency: "50% off this week only"]"
```

#### 👥 Community Content Formula
```
BUILD-IN-PUBLIC Framework:
B - Background: Why you're building this
U - Update: What you shipped this week
I - Insight: What you learned
L - Link: Try it / contribute
D - Discussion: Ask for feedback

Example:
"🛠️ Week [N] of building [Product] in public
This week: [feature shipped]
Learned: [insight]
Try it: [link]
What feature would YOU want next?"
```

### Channel-Specific Content (Localized)

#### 🇻🇳 Vietnam — Channels Deep Dive

**Facebook (phổ biến nhất — 70M+ users VN)**
```
Post format:
- Hook: 1-2 câu kích thích (câu hỏi hoặc stat gây sốc)
- Story: 3-5 câu storytelling personal
- Value: 3 bullet points lợi ích
- CTA: Link + urgency
- Hashtags: 5-7 relevant
Best time: 11h-13h (lunch), 19h-21h (tối)
Tần suất: 3-5 posts/tuần
```

**TikTok (GenZ + 25-35 — 50M+ users VN)**
```
Video Script Template (15-60s):
[0-3s] HOOK: "Bạn có biết..." / "Tháng nào cũng..."
[3-8s] PROBLEM: Amplify pain point
[8-20s] SOLUTION: Demo app (screen record)
[20-25s] PROOF: "500 người đã dùng"
[25-30s] CTA: "Link ở bio — miễn phí!"
Trending sounds: Dùng nhạc trending VN
Hashtags: #fyp #xuhuong #app #congnghe
Best time: 18h-22h
Tần suất: 1 video/ngày (tuần launch)
```

**Zalo OA (professional — 75M+ users VN)**
```
Dùng cho: B2B, professional tools
Format: Article dài, hữu ích
Tần suất: 1-2 bài/tuần
Best for: Nurture existing users
```

#### 🇯🇵 Japan — Channels Deep Dive

**Twitter/X (tech community — 60M+ users JP)**
```
Thread format (5-7 tweets):
Tweet 1: [Hook + emoji] "〇〇で困っていませんか？"
Tweet 2-5: Solution details (1 point per tweet)
Tweet 6: Demo screenshot/video
Tweet 7: CTA + link
Hashtags: #開発 #プログラミング #個人開発
Best time: 12h, 18h-22h JST
```

**note.com (long-form — JP Medium alternative)**
```
Article format: Detailed, polished, story-driven
Tone: 丁寧語 (polite), personal story
Length: 2000-4000 characters
Best for: Building authority, SEO
```

**Qiita (developer community — JP Stack Overflow)**
```
Technical tutorial format
Must be: High quality, code examples, reproducible
Best for: Developer tools, OSS projects
```

#### 🇨🇳 China — Channels Deep Dive

**WeChat 公众号 (official account — 1.3B users)**
```
Article format: Long-form (2000+ chars)
Tone: Authoritative, data-driven
Visuals: Heavy use of images, infographics
Best time: 20h-22h
Promotion: Share to WeChat groups, moments
```

**小红书 Xiaohongshu (lifestyle — 300M+ users)**
```
Format: Image carousel (6-9 images) + short text
Style: Aesthetic, lifestyle-focused
Best for: Consumer apps, design-heavy products
Hashtags: #科技 #好物推荐 #APP推荐
```

#### 🌍 Global — Channels Deep Dive

**Product Hunt (CRITICAL for global launch)**
```
PREPARATION (2-4 weeks before):
1. Research hunters — reach out to influential ones
2. Build PH community presence (comment, upvote daily)
3. Prepare assets:
   - Tagline: max 60 chars, value-driven, no buzzwords
   - Description: 3 paragraphs (problem, solution, differentiator)
   - Images: 5 high-quality screenshots (1200x900px)
   - Video: 45-90s demo (optional but recommended)
   - Maker comment: Personal story + vision + "ask me anything"

LAUNCH DAY:
- Time: 12:01 AM Pacific Time
- Day: Tuesday-Thursday (higher traffic)
- First hour: Reach out to supporters (NOT "please upvote")
  → "We just launched on PH, would love your feedback!"
- All day: Respond to EVERY comment within 15 min
- Share milestones: "Top 5!"  "200 upvotes!"

POST-LAUNCH:
- Thank everyone publicly
- Badge on website: "Product of the Day"
- Repurpose content for other channels
```

**Hacker News (Show HN)**
```
Title: "Show HN: [Product] – [what it does in plain terms]"
Rules:
- Be humble, ask for feedback
- NO marketing speak
- Technical details welcome
- Respond to every comment
- Post on weekday mornings EST
```

**Reddit**
```
Subreddit strategy:
- r/sideproject (always OK)
- r/[relevant niche] (check rules first)
- r/webdev, r/startups, r/indiehackers (if relevant)
Format: Genuine story, ask for feedback, NOT salesy
Timing: weekday mornings, vary by subreddit
```

**Dev.to / Hashnode (developer blogs)**
```
Format: "How I built [X] — tech stack, lessons, results"
Include: Code snippets, architecture decisions, metrics
Cross-post: Same article on both platforms for reach
```

